Degtyarev was surprised by the information about the purchase of gas “Sakhalin-1” for dollars
Acting Governor of the Khabarovsk Territory Mikhail Degtyarev on Sunday, July 26, during a meeting with residents of Soviet Harbor, was surprised that the region buys Sakhalin gas, produced by the American company Exxon Neftegas, for dollars.
American gas is contracted in dollars until 2025.
“Honestly, I didn’t know it, and I’m in such a knockdown because of this information.
I had no idea that such a thing is still possible in 2020 in Russia,” RIA Novosti quoted him as saying.
Degtyarev noted that this issue was discussed with the head of the Ministry of Energy of Russia Alexander Novak during his visit to Khabarovsk on July 24.
The acting governor also stressed that by 2025, Gazprom is switching to the supply of Russian thermal power plants and capacities, which means that Russian gas purchased in rubles “at normal prices” will be used.
The Sakhalin-1 project is implemented through a production sharing agreement, where Exxon Neftegas Ltd is the operator of the project with a share of 30%, Rosneft has another 20%, Sodeco has a share of 30% and India’s ONGC has a share of 20%.
Khabarovsk Krai has been acquiring gas from this project since 2005.
