A woman threw her husband’s body into a hole and poured concrete near Belgorod
In the Belgorod region, the woman confessed to the murder of her husband, whom she threw into a pit with waste and poured concrete, according to the website of the regional administration of the Investigative Committee of the Russian Federation.
It is noted that the suspect lived in a marriage with the deceased since 1999.
In recent years, the husband began to abuse alcohol and after another quarrel, the woman decided to kill.
“When the husband fell asleep, the suspect tied his hands and feet, put a plastic bag on his head and pressed a pillow.
When the husband ceased to show signs of life, she wrapped the body in a carpet, carried it to the yard and hid it in a cesspool.
The next day, she called a concrete mixer and poured concrete into the pit," the department said.
Later, the woman reported that her husband was missing.
Relatives of the deceased went to the police, who opened the hole and removed the body.
The investigation intends to ask the court to arrest the suspect.
The criminal investigation is ongoing.
